# ArcEsriFeatureLayer + ArcGeoJson Migration Changelog
# ArcGIS 3.x → ArcGIS Maps SDK 5.x Compatibility Guide

Version: 2.x

Purpose:
Provide backward compatibility support between ArcGIS 3.x and ArcGIS Maps SDK 5.x while preserving consumer APIs for ArcEsriFeatureLayer and ArcGeoJson.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 1 — OVERVIEW
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Supported compatibility:

✓ ArcGIS 3.x renderers
✓ ArcGIS Maps SDK 5.x renderers
✓ ArcEsriFeatureLayer
✓ ArcGeoJson
✓ Label JSON
✓ Symbol normalization
✓ Old → New renderer conversion
✓ Backward compatibility support

Goal:

Consumer applications written with older Esri syntax should continue to work
without requiring changes.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 2 — RENDERER TYPE MIGRATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Old Type                                        New Type

simple                                          simple
uniqueValue                                     unique-value
classBreaks                                     class-breaks

SimpleRenderer                                  simple
UniqueValueRenderer                             unique-value
ClassBreaksRenderer                             class-breaks

esri.renderers.SimpleRenderer                   simple
esri.renderers.UniqueValueRenderer              unique-value
esri.renderers.ClassBreaksRenderer              class-breaks


Example:

OLD

{
   type:"uniqueValue"
}

NEW

{
   type:"unique-value"
}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 3 — RENDERER FIELD MIGRATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Old Property                                    New Property

field1                                          field
field2                                          field2
field3                                          field3

Example:

OLD

{
   field1:"SBDV_NAME"
}

NEW

{
   field:"SBDV_NAME"
}

Internal normalization:

field1 → field

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SECTION 4 — LINE SYMBOL MIGRATION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Old Symbol:

type:"esriSLS"

New Symbol:

type:"simple-line"

Style migration:

esriSLSSolid                 → solid
esriSLSDash                  → dash
esriSLSDot                   → dot
esriSLSDashDot               → dash-dot
esriSLSDashDotDot            → dash-dot-dot
esriSLSShortDash             → short-dash
esriSLSShortDot              → short-dot
esriSLSShortDashDot          → short-dash-dot
esriSLSShortDashDotDot       → short-dash-dot-dot
esriSLSLongDash              → long-dash
esriSLSLongDashDot           → long-dash-dot
esriSLSNull                  → none


Example:

OLD

{
   type:"esriSLS",
   style:"esriSLSShortDash"
}

NEW

{
   type:"simple-line",
   style:"short-dash"
}

